      "acceptanceCriteria": "Not required at MRL 2; model form selection is documented with literature justification.",
      "rationale": "The Giersiepen-Wurzinger power-law hemolysis model is selected based on published benchmark comparisons for rotary blood pumps. Formal model form uncertainty quantification is not required at MRL 2."
    },
    {
      "factorStandard": "ASME-VV40-2018",
      "factorType": "Model inputs",
      "type": "CredibilityFactor",
      "requiredLevel": 2,
      "achievedLevel": 2,
      "factorStatus": "assessed",
      "acceptanceCriteria": "All model inputs are sourced from measurements or published material data with documented uncertainty bounds. Comprehensive Monte Carlo UQ propagates input variability through the model.",
      "rationale": "Blood viscosity, density, and hemolysis model coefficients were assigned probability distributions based on published literature ranges and in-house measurements. A comprehensive Monte Carlo sampling scheme (n=500 Latin hypercube samples) was executed across all uncertain inputs to produce probabilistic distributions of NIH and RH. The 95th-percentile RH remained below 0.93, confirming robustness of the acceptance criterion under input variability."
    },
